This paper discusses the design of integrated access and backhaul (IAB) networks for mmWave frequencies, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses path selection techniques and channel models, which are related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the harsh propagation environment at mmWave frequencies, which is a topic related to signal processing and communication systems, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.COMM (Communications) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses distributed approaches to path selection, which is a topic related to multi-agent systems and distributed algorithms, making cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) a possible category.
